condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section 1 (B) (i) | Description :The Borrower, through MESD, shall maintain the PMU duringProjectimplementation with adequate staffing and resources satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (A) | Description :The Borrower shall maintain the Inter-Ministerial Committee for theApplication of Nitrates during Project implementation. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (A) | Description :The Borrower, through MESD, shall assign responsibility for overallprojectoversight to the Inter-Ministerial Committee for Application of the Nitrates Directive (ICA). | Due Date :13-Oct-2008

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (B) (ii) | Description :Not later than three (3) months after the Effectiveness Deadline,theBorrower, through MESD, shall hire suchspecialists as required for effective project implementation. | Due Date :25-Feb-2009

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (C) | Description :The Borrower, through the MESD, shall causethe first six (6) selectedWater Basin Directorates to hire one or two staff to work onProject implementation at the regional level. | Due Date :24-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (C) | Description :Within thenext six months, the remaining Water Basin Directoratesshall hire one or two staff towork on Project implementation at the regional level. | Due Date :24-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (D)(i) | Description :The Borrower, through MESD, shall take all necessary measurestoimplement the Project in accordance with the Operational Manual and EMP, and shallnot change either document without Bankapproval. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (D)(ii) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that all measures necessaryunder the EMPare carried out in a timely manner. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (D)(iii) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that adequate information onimplementation of the EMP is included in the Project Reports referred to in Section II.A of Schedule 2 | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (E) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that appropriate budget allocations are madeavailable yearly for the Project implementation purposes, throughout the Project life. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (F)(i) | Description :The Borrower shall select the Beneficiaries and Sub-projects basedon the selection criteriaset forth in the Operational Manual. | Due Date :22-Sep-2008

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (F)(ii) | Description :The Borrower shall provide funds from the Loan proceeds to selectedBeneficiaries foreligible Sub-projects on terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (F)(iii) | Description :The Borrower shall enter into contractual arrangements withBeneficiaries for provision offunds for Sub-projects which shall set forth the terms and conditions forthese funds. | Frequency:Yearly
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (F)(iv) | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that Sub-projects are implemented inaccordance with the Operational Manual and the EMP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (G)(1) | Description :Not later than thirty (30) months after the Effectiveness Deadline,the Borrower,through the MESD, shall carry out jointly with the Bank, a midterm review of theproject. | Due Date :31-May-2011

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (G)(2) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall prepare at least 4 weeks before the MTR,send the Bank a report on the status ofimplementation of each component and a summary report of overallimplementation. | Due Date:31-Mar-2011

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I (G)(3) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall, not later than 2 weeks after the MTR,prepare and submit to the Bank an action program for the further implementation of the Project, and implement such action program.| Due Date :28-Jun-2012

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section II (A) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall monitor and evaluate the progress of theProject and prepare Project Reports on the basis of indicators agreed with the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section II (B)(1) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall maintain a financial management system inaccordance with the General Conditions. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section II (B)(2) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall prepare and furnish to WB no later than45 days after the end of each calendar semester, interim un-audited financial reports covering the semester, satisfactory to theBank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section II (B)(3) | Description :The Borrower (MESD) shall have its Financial Statements audited inaccordance with the General Conditions, covering 1 FY and furnish it to the Bank no later than 6 months after the end of the FY. |Frequency :Yearly
